WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'Labyzarre' is a Workbench game played on a 10 by 10 grid, that
is surrounded by a wall. There are two doors: en entry door,
located at the top of the game area and an exit at the bottom of
the grid. The goal of the game is to go from the entry point to
the exit, you must move to every square of the grid and you cannot
go to an already passed square. When you move, a path will be
drawn on the squares you visited. The game ends if you 'trap'
yourself in a dead-end (between walls, blocks and/or already
visited squares).

  The game features two playing mode, a "Normal" (or 'practice')
game and a game with "Blocks", which you have to go around...

  Have fun!

